This paper deals with the analysis of the performance metrics of unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV)-aided terrestrial cellular networks, which involves the use of wireless communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of interference and other performance metrics, which can be related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. The use of UAVs in cellular networks can also be considered as a control system, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves the use of mobile UAVs for data transmission, which can be related to multimedia applications, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of error recovery protocols, which can be related to computer security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
